headline: ‘Application day’ nears for UP-NS rail merger
summary: Union Pacific and Norfolk Southern will file their formal merger application Friday with the Surface Transportation Board, detailing historic plans for the first transcontinental railroad. The post ‘Application day’ nears for UP-NS rail merger appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: Union Pacific and Norfolk Southern Announce Analyst Call to Review STB Merger Application to Create America’s First Transcontinental Railroad
summary: OMAHA, Neb. & ATLANTA, December 18, 2025--Union Pacific and Norfolk Southern will submit their application to the Surface Transportation Board (STB) Friday, Dec. 19, 2025, requesting approval to combine the two railroads and create America’s first transcontinental railroad. Both companies’ management teams will co-host a conference call and live webcast at 8:45 a.m. ET.

headline: Norfolk Southern (NSC): Evaluating Valuation After a Strong Year-to-Date Share Price Rally
summary: Norfolk Southern (NSC) has quietly moved higher this month, and that steady climb has investors revisiting whether the railroad’s improving fundamentals justify the current valuation after a strong year to date rally. See our latest analysis for Norfolk Southern. Zooming out, the stock’s 25.53% year to date share price return and 26.49% one year total shareholder return suggest momentum is still building as investors grow more comfortable with its earnings trajectory and rail demand...
